==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Jonquille
<hw>Jon"quille</hw> }</mhw>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[F. <ets>jonquille</ets>, fr. L. <ets>juncus</ets> a rush, because
it has rushlike leaves.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A bulbous plant of
the genus <gen>Narcissus</gen> (<spn>Narcissus Jonquilla</spn>), allied
to the daffodil. It has long, rushlike leaves, and yellow or white
fragrant flowers. The root has emetic properties. It is sometimes called
the <altname>rush-leaved daffodil</altname>. See <xex>Illust.</xex> of
<er>Corona</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Joram</ent>⟦br⟧
